name: PrintEncoding
shortdesc: Encoding to use when printing PostScript.

property.name: BINARY
property.shortdesc: Binary encoding. Some print spooler programs, computer networks, and third-party printer drivers don't support binary files.

property.name: JPEG
property.shortdesc: JPEG encoding. JPEG-encoded files are smaller than binary files and take less time to print; however, image quality is decreased. Only PostScrpt Level 2 or higher printers support JPEG encoding. Some print spooler programs, computer networks, and third-party printer drivers don't support JPEG-encoded files.

property.name: ASCII
property.shortdesc: ASCII85 encoding. ASCII85 files contain about twice as many characters and take twice as long to transfer as binary files.
